async_hooks are instrumented by chrome devtools to capture good async stack traces. Profiling with `node --prof` does not show such usage. If I disable async stack traces from chrome devtools options I confirm it doesn't show such usage either.

This can be recreated just with this code

```ts
(async function test() {
  for (let i = 0; i < Infinity; i++) {
    await new Promise((r) => {
      r();
    });
